Content Security Policy (CSP) is a security feature that helps prevent cross-site scripting (XSS) and other code injection attacks. It is implemented by setting an HTTP response header named "Content-Security-Policy" in your server configuration or at the application level. In a Java web application, you can add the CSP header within your Java code, typically in a Servlet Filter or even in a specific Servlet or Controller.

Here's an example of a simple CSP header implementation in Java using a Servlet Filter:

